description:
How do I love thee, McTeague's? Let me count the ways:

1. The moment I walked through the door, an adorable handlebar-mustashioed bartender greeted me in a sincerely cheery way...YAY for cute boys greeting me cheerily;

2. I have no idea what that music was that was playing on the jukebox, but, DAMMIT, it was good...ALL of it;

3. The longer I sat there, the more I started to forget which decade I was in, which city I was in...it was like I was in Anytown, USA;

4. My Hornitos shots were filled to the BRIM...to the very BRIM; and

5. All around me there was interesting conversation upon which to eavesdrop.

I have a feeling I'll be darkening your doorstep again very soon, McTeague's.
